title: 15 min Daily Yoga Flow | Balance & Flexibility
description:
Welcome to this 15-minute daily full body focused yoga flow designed to bring some nourishing me-time during your festive season üßò‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è‚ú®

Start your practice seated as we gently warm up the wrists, shoulders, and spine, setting the foundation for a nourishing practice. Transition into standing postures, building some heat through postures like Warrior Three, Half Moon, and the (hopefully!) playful 'tying the shoelaces' or 'putting a climbing shoe on' balance. My invitation is to embrace those wobbles as we stand on one foot, lifting the opposite knee as high as we can.

As we wind down, return to a seated position for passive stretches. Explore a gentle chest opener and a forward fold, release tension with side bends. Finishing the moving part of the practice with hip 'openers'. 

Conclude this daily flow in a relaxation position, allowing the body to settle, breathing through the nose üåü‚ú®

title: 10 min Dynamic & Fluid Flow üçØ | Playful Full Body Yoga
description:
Welcome to this 10-minute dynamic and fluid flow, focusing on the entire body. My invitation is to invite a quality of fluidity into your practice, as if you're moving through water or honey. üçØ

In this practice, we start in a seated position to bring awareness to the breath, explore twists, warm up the wrists, and eventually transitioning to a standing positions/movements. 

We explore the quality of fluidity by moving without stopping form one position to the other. As if going through the loop. No destination, just exploring the process and the journey. How does it feel like to move fluidly from one asana to the other? Remember, there is no right or wrong answer. 

There is also some quick core activation in this practice.

Finishing in a seated position, checking in with how you feel in this moment, post-practice.

Thank you for practicing together. üôè

title: 25 min Full body routine | Approved by physio Jason from Hooper's Beta | Yoga for Climbers
description:
Join me for a 25-minute follow-along full-body routine designed specifically for climbers, in collaboration with the physical therapist Jason from Hooper's Beta.

In this yoga inspired class for climbers, we will focus on building strength and flexibility in these key areas of the body: knees, hips, spine, and shoulders. We will also activate the core and also playfully challenge ourselves with some balance postures on one foot. 

Throughout the routine, there will be various options to incorporate a weight for added challenge - so grab that if you'd like to make some of the movements harder. Starting from a comfortable seated position with quick finger and wrist warm up, we will then move through dynamic and static postures, such as squats, half moon, warrior 3, goddess pose, high lunge with the spine rotation (and more!) combining strength-building and mobility-enhancing movements.

This routine is a thoughtful blend of yoga-inspired movements, strength exercises, and flexibility drills, ensuring an effective workout designed to the needs of climbers. 

*****

For in-depth videos on injury recovery and training for climbers by a physical therapist, make sure to check out Hooper‚Äôs Beta YouTube channel. Link below!

title: Day 1 - Grounded Leg Strength | 7 days of Strength through yoga & mobility | üìç Esu Dabar studio
description:
Welcome to 7 days of strength series where we will be exploring strength within our bodies through yoga postures, movement and mobility exercises! 

I invite you to show up 7 days in a row, for around 15 to 20 mins per day. Each day we will focus on a different part of the body exploring the strength and mobility in that area. 

On Day 1 we focus on the lower body - hips, hamstrings, thighs and calves. First exploring different variations of the 90/90 to warm up the legs, specifically the hip area, following with balance standing postures such as squeezing the block with the heel and glute to activate the hamstrings and calves.

Playing with standing splits and pistol squats, as always embracing those wobbles.  

Finishing with a couple of mindful breaths. 

Showing up consistently is beautiful.. and powerfulüî•

Thank you for practising together. 

*****

title: 20 min Strong & Dynamic Flow | Full Body Yoga with Emphasis on Shoulders & Legs
description:
Join me for this 20 minute strong and dynamic yoga flow where we use the block/brick or a similar object. It's a full body class with a focus on the arms, shoulders as well as legs. 

Throughout the whole class we are holding the object in between our hands to invite some novelty into the movement and to spice the practice up. 

From shoulder joint halo's to passing the block around the body in the beginning of the practice in a seated position to then exploring standing postures (such as warrior three, high lunge, warrior two) while still holding the block in between the hands. 

As always, harmonising the movement with your unique rhythm of the breath, exploring the body, the movement, and hopefully playfully challenging ourselves through this flow. 

*****

I had so much fun filming this session and I hope you enjoy it as well! 

*****

title: Full Body Stretching routine | 25 min Flexibility Yoga for Climbers | No standing |üìçKalymnos
description:
Welcome to this 25 min full body stretching routine that is perfect after climbing, before bedtime or whenever you'd like to take it slow and stretch ü•∞ 

This class has no standing postures, we do all the movements on the ground in a seated position, laying on the back and on all four.

We start the practice with spine flexion and extension, gentle neck stretches, followed by puppy pose, spine twist as well as various stretches for hamstrings, hips and thighs. 

Hope you enjoy this nourishing routine!

*****

title: 40 min Calming Recovery Yin Yoga after Climbing | Slow and gentle floor practice | No standing
description:
Join me for this super slow 40 min yin yoga session. There are few things to keep in mind:

- We will be holding the positions passively
- Supporting the body with pillows/ other props (going only 70% of your maximum)
- Gentle, calm breathing through the nose
- Rebound/Neutral position after each posture to observe the body

title: After Climbing PNF Upper Body Stretching Routine @ Patxi Usobiaga's The Temple Climbing Gym
description:
Follow along PNF inspired Upper Body Stretching Routine! This will be juicy, friendsü¶Å

PNF is a 'contract - relax your muscles' method, which is best done AFTER a training, climbing etc. session when you are properly warmed up. 

The research paper says that if done several days per week it might increase your range of motion (ROM) and flexibility.

However, if done prior to the exercise PNF routine might decrease your performance of high intensity exercises where maximal muscle effort is required. For example if you want to lift weights, climb, jump - do the PNF stretching routine after your training session, not before.

description:

Each day I invite you to do three things:

title: 20 min Hip Mobility: 10 exercises for strong & flexible hips | improve your high stepping & frogging
description:
Join me for this follow along Hip Mobility routine where I share 10 exercises/movements that if done regularly could help you improve your hip strength and flexibility and as a result might help to improve your high stepping & frogging while rock climbing üê∏

This practice is only 20 min long, divided in 10 exercises: 

1. Accordeon 0:50-2:00
2. 90/90 variations 2:00-7:13
3. Butterfly bridge 7:24-8:32
4. Knee towards upper arm 9:02-12:10
5. Hip rotations 12:28-12:59
6. Squeeze the block 13:00-15:05
7. Cossack squat 15:20-17:40
8. Squeeze the imaginary balloon 18:00-20:24
9. Squat 20:28-21:21
10. Drop knees 21:22-21:47


I also wrote an article for Training Beta that goes slightly in more depth about the hip flexibility and strength and it's importance for climbing. You can read the article below:

https://www.trainingbeta.com/hip-mobility-for-rock-climbers/

Big virtual hug to you all üíö

title: 15 min Warm-Up Flow for Climbing | Yoga for Climbers
description:
Join me for a 15 min Warm-Up Flow for Climbing üåä

In this session I share some ideas that you can incorporate into your warm up before climbing routine. 

Warm up should consist of three parts:

1. Create heat in your body/ Increase your heart rate (jump rope, sun salutations, cycling, etc)
2. Rotate your joints (controlled arm, hip circles etc), activate your muscles and do some active stretching (leave static stretching after climbing or for your rest day)
3. Easy climbing on the wall 

How do you usually warm up before climbing? Share in the comments below!

title: 35 min Antagonist Flow for Shoulder, Arm & Wrist Strength and Health | Yoga for Climbers
description:
Join me for a 35 min Antagonist Yoga Flow for Shoulder, Arm & Wrist Strength and Health designed for Climbersüåõ

In climbing we pull with our biceps more than we push with our triceps (unless there are lots of mantle moves in the climbing routeüôà). 

To keep our shoulders, elbows and wrists healthy, balance between push and pull is necessary. Therefore, in this Antagonist Yoga practice, on the contrary to climbing, we will push the ground away from us.

There will be few options where you could add a little resistance band around your fingers or take some weights into your hands to make the movement harder.

P.s. If you are climbing, do you strengthen your pushing muscles? If you are practising yoga asana, do you train your pulling muscles?

Enjoy the practice and as always, let me know what you think üíö

title: 20 min Core Strength Flow | Yoga for Climbers
description:
Join me for this quick 20 min flow that focuses on our core strength üî•

We will fire up our abdominals, obliques, TVA (deep core muscles) as well as glutes, hip flexors and back muscles. So, yes, core is more than our abs! It is our whole midsection, the centre of our body.

Strong core improves our posture, stabilises and supports our body in all daily activities. In rock climbing, our core activates every time we pull, dyno, high step or do rock overs. Strong core provides stability, helps to bring our legs back on the wall on overhanging terrain and allows to keep our body closer to the vertical wall. 

Enjoy the session, and as always - let me know how it goes üßòüèΩ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è

title: 50 min Yoga for Climbers: Active Recovery for a Rest Day
description:
Join me for a 52 min yoga session that is designed for rest days‚ú®

With this lower intensity yoga routine for climbers, you will strengthen your non-climbing muscles to maintain muscular balance. You will also lengthen tighter spots as well as massage your palms, forearms and shoulders that might feel tense after a climbing session.

During the practice, remind yourself to breathe calmly, steady and lightly in order to relax your parasympathetic nervous system (rest and digest response instead of fight and flight).

description:

It's a slower practice (compared to some of my other sessions), where we focus on our breath, explore the movement of the body and bring the awareness to the present moment üôèüèΩ üíö You should also feel your hamstrings, calfs and gluteus working üî•

In rock climbing strong back body helps us to heel hook, to keep our feet on the wall as well as to push through that foothold when we want to reach a higher handhold above. Strong posterior chain might also help to prevent lower back, knee and hamstring injuries.

title: Prenatal Yoga Workout | 30 Min Full Body Pregnancy Safe Workout ‚ù§ ALL TRIMESTERS
description:
After this gentle pregnancy safe 30 min prenatal yoga workout for all trimesters, check out the complete Boho Beautiful Prenatal Journey Program - https://bohobeautiful.life/prenatal

This full body rejuvenation workout was designed for all expecting mothers in all trimesters to enjoy yoga and fitness while pregnant. We will start with a prenatal safe core workout, glutes, legs & finish with the upper body.  Remember to listen to your body, breathe deeply, and avoid any movement or posture that doesn't feel right in this moment in your life.

It is incredibly important to listen to your body at all stages of your journey, bringing life into the world. If it is telling you to sit out, a stretch doesn't feel right at this time, or part way through if you need to stop completely... all of this is PERFECTLY ok, and you should listen and understand that this is just how you are in this moment right now.  If you try again in an hour, or a day, or a week, it is incredibly likely your body then will give you different messages based on where you are at then too. 

So experiment with yourself. Listen carefully. Drink lots of water. And take this well deserved 30 minutes to let go and just have fun. :)

title: 30 Min Prenatal Yoga Workout | Gentle Pregnancy Safe Workout & Stretch For All Expecting Mothers ‚ù§
description:
After this pregnancy safe 30 min prenatal yoga workout for all trimesters, check out the complete Boho Beautiful Prenatal Journey Program - https://bohobeautiful.life/prenatal

This class was designed for expecting mothers in all trimesters to enjoy yoga & fitness while pregnant. Through a series of completely pregnancy safe and customizable exercises and stretches, we will gently push our body to release tension, stress, and any sore muscles or unbalanced aspect of our entire beings. 

It is incredibly important to listen to your body at all stages of your journey, bringing life into the world. If it is telling you to sit out, a stretch doesn't feel right at this time, or part way through if you need to stop completely... all of this is PERFECTLY ok, and you should listen and understand that this is just how you are in this moment right now.  If you try again in an hour, or a day, or a week, it is incredibly likely your body then will give you different messages based on where you are at then too. 

So experiment with yourself. Listen carefully. Drink lots of water. And take this well deserved 30 minutes to let go and just have fun. :)

title: Yin Yoga for Upper Body | Release ALL Stress & Tension In 30 Minutes
description:
This 30 minute upper body Yin Yoga class will provide immediate relief for your sore or painful upper back, neck, shoulders, arms, and chest. Through a series of mindfully deep muscle releasing asanas in this Boho Beautiful Yoga sequence, Mark Spicoluk will provide you the tools & space necessary to target all that is no longer serving you in order to first recognize it, then breathe through it, and finally ... find your liberation.  

Yin Yoga is about breath. It's about following your breath to create the space necessary to ultimately reconnect to your inner stillness. Inside that stillness yin yoga allows you to cultivate peace with whatever is going on inside both your mind and body surrounding that stillness, in order to find acceptance, forgiveness, and then ultimately complete deliverance from it. 

So throughout this class, remember to use your breath as the string to guide you back to your deliberate attention and conscious awareness ... for those are the gateway to all that you are looking for. 

So grab your mat, and some water, and don't forget to work hard and have fun. 

Yoga Instructor: Mark Spicoluk
Location: Costa Rica

description:

title: Gentle Evening Yoga | 20 Min Bedtime Yoga To Wind Down & Wash Away Stress
description:
This 20 minute bedtime yoga to wind down is the evening yoga class to gently let go of all that no longer serves you.

title: How To Headstand & What To NEVER EVER Do! | Headstand For Beginners Masterclass
description:
Anyone can learn to do a headstand and this beginners step by step tutorial will show you exactly that. Salamba Sirsasana comes first through strength building, then balance, and always safety ... and no matter what level of yogi you are this Boho Beautiful yoga class can guide you to a perfect headstand execution. 

One of the main ideas of inversions like this is to experiment with your body and have fun. Yes, thats right ... just like when we were all kids the idea is to find joy in both being upside down and falling from time to time. Both are ideas for many years now, most of us have been told we grow out of, however when we reintegrate them into our lives with joy, curiosity, and self love a whole new and familiar world opens up. 

So please 
Remember to listen to your body... 
DON'T push past your comfort zone.
AND make sure to put your weight on your arms NOT your actual head!
and most of all have fun. 
Because headstands aren't just for the young, they are also for the young at heart!

Grab your mat, and don't forget to 
work hard & have fun.

title: 15 MIN Yoga Workout  For Beginners | Gentle Strength Building Or Getting Back In Shape
description:
This short 15 min beginner yoga workout class is perfect for beginning your journey or starting to get back into shape again. A well-rounded, gentle, and laid-back full body workout for easing back onto your mat and laying the groundwork for the journey to come. 

Remember, this class is a guide, let it show you the path but make sure you listen to your body and work your way to what feels best. If a certain exercise doesn't feel right or is too much right now, do what you can but don't be afraid to sit it out and then pick up on the next exercise. Then the next time you come to do this class you can do a little more, and the next time after that a little more. 
Everybody is at a different point on their journey. 
And where you are in this moment is perfect for you and only you!

Grab some water, and let's get on our mats!

title: 15 Minute Guided Meditation | Clear & Calm The Mind In Uncertain Times

title: 25 Min Yin Yoga Class | 7 Day Yin Yoga Exploration Challenge
description:
In under 30 minutes a day, take yourself on a beautiful exploration of the style of Yin Yoga and how it can provide your body and mind everything you didn't even know you needed and more. 
Click here to get the FREE 7 Day Yin Yoga Exploration Schedule: https://bohobeautiful.life/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Yin-Yoga-Schedule.pdf

And find dozens more yin practices on The Boho Beautiful App: https://www.bohobeautiful.app

This 30 minute Yin Yoga class for everyone is a perfect way to relax your body and mind and let go of any unwanted tension in your muscles. This easy and gentle yin yoga practice is a beautiful way to deeply stretch your body after a long day, or help let go of any stress and negative energy that may be stored within you. 

This slow and restorative yin yoga practice will not only release physical soreness and stiffness but also welcome any release of emotional and mental stress that you may be holding within the hips and lower body. It's important to surrender to each yin yoga posture and accept any type of emotional release that may come your way. Be patient with your body and let go. 

Remember, breathing is a very important factor in any Yin Yoga class, so through out this entire practice, make sure you're taking deep breaths in and long, slow exhales out. Bring oxygen to your muscles, organs, and mind. Re-energize your nervous system, let go of stress and tension, and become fully present in each moment of each posture as you let go of the past with each exhale you make. 

Roll out that mat and enjoy! XO

title: Yoga Justice Warriors- Stay Back | The Journey, Ascension, & Division Of Yoga
description:
Yoga is about union. Not Division. 
My soul honours your soul, in seeing the light and energy within you I recognize that it is also within me, and in this we are the same. We are one. Namaste

On or off our yoga mats, each and every one of us is on our special personal journey. Yoga can be an incredible tool to further our personal growth. It in all forms can aid us to find a deeper connection within, no matter what the "method' or 'style' we practice. With the recent popularization of yoga throughout the west and many people, including ourselves, incorporating it into our own personal livelihood, it triggers a lot of negativity from people who believe it's "their way or the highway". We want to share our opinion on the so-called "yoga justice warriors" who feel ok to expel their negativity and division onto others.

title: Best Stretches For Back Pain Relief | How To Cure Back Pain
description:
These effective stretches for back pain relief are an easy and gentle path to recovery, healing, and back pain prevention. By incorporating these beginner yoga postures and movements each day, you can start rehabilitating and healing your sore back and aching or tight muscles. 

Whether you are recovering from disk herniation, sciatica pain, or any other back pain & discomfort, these yoga asanas, stretches, and exercises will slowly guide your body to better health and well-being. 

Some great yoga classes for relieving back pain:

Back Pain & Sciatica Relief
https://youtu.be/eiQjt0WSVHk

Yoga For Your Back | Strength, Recover, & Tone 
https://youtu.be/H6IsIWlSVkA

By doing these back pain relief stretches and strengthening exercises for back pain and discomfort, we will slowly bring more blood flow and oxygen into the joints and muscle tissues. 

Remember to go slow and listen to your body. If you believe you are suffering from a more serious injury like disk herniation, bulging disks, sciatica, or any other more serious injuries, PLEASE consult your doctor or physical therapist to make sure these exercises and postures are right for you. Back injury is a very serious condition that must not be taken lightly; thus if you begin to experience any shooting or sharp pain, stop the exercise and talk to your doctor before beginning any exercise.

title: Wrist Pain During Yoga & Workouts | HOW TO DEAL WITH IT
description:
Wrist pain during yoga and mat based fitness is a common problem. 
We get so many questions asking how to deal with wrist pain, how to cure it, and how to manage it so we created this wrist pain tutorial video for anyone that is looking for an answer. 

Why do my wrists hurt during yoga? How do I strengthen the wrists? What can I do when my wrists become weak and begin to hurt during yoga? How do I hold my planks without wrist pain? 

A lot of the time people experience wrist pain in planks, downward dogs, chaturangas, or just generally when bearing a lot of body weight on their hands. There are ways to cope with this wrist pain by using different wrist strengthening exercises, and wrists stretching movements and postures. 

Try to include these different wrist pain solutions before or after your yoga practice and/or workouts. With time and patience the pain will get less as the body gets stronger. 

We took 10 minutes on set of our new program Boho Beautiful Retreat (http://www.bohobeautiful.life/retreat) and answered some of your questions and concerns about everything to do with wrist pain and how to manage it.

title: Dreams, Vision Boards, & How To Take Back Control in 2020
description:
This new year 2020 is a perfect opportunity to set your dreams, visions, and goals back up and in the direction you want. For the last seven years, we have been implementing one strategy to take back control of our lives, which at the beginning of this wild ride together seemed so far out of step with what we really wanted from our life. 

But it's not a race. It's clarity. It's creating a map. And every day, checking back in on whether or not you are still on course, and then making slight adjustments always. Getting where or what you want out of life, and becoming the person you believe you can be, is a quiet and slow process of many steps. And it is a constant battle with falling down or out of step, understanding it to be a part of the journey, and then recognizing the changes to your behaviour you have to make to get back on track again. Acceptance, forgiveness, perseverance, and most of all: grace. 

That's why every new year, we create a vision board. Also known as a dream board, this single strategy has allowed us to slowly and methodically design a life and a design for ourselves as people that we are proud to constantly be walking towards. It's not magic. There is no secret. And it takes intense amounts of patience, belief, and determination. 

But most of all after this many years I think the most important idea is that we have found a deep surrender to the process... because the process is the journey... and if you get too comfortable the journey can so easily take control of you, so once in a while you have to spend a little time remembering where it is you want to go, so that you can take back control of it.

title: Finally Able To Share This With You!
description:
With all the unfortunate events descending on the planet 2020 has been an incredibly strange and unsettling year for a lot of people. We cannot control the events, but we can control how we feel about them. Take this opportunity to come back to yourself. Take back control of your year and join us on the mat for a journey through yoga. 

Experience the world's first virtual yoga retreat from the comfort of your own home - Available to stream and download in "Netflix style" web browser, and iOS & Android App!
 
Step on your mat and dive deeper into your own personal practice of mind-body connection. 
Find the peace we all need now, and disconnect to reconnect. ‚òÆ

Boho Beautiful Retreat
Learn more here:  https://www.bohobeautiful.life/retreat
Available to download/stream via "Netflix style" web browsing, and iOS & Android App!

Over the years, the two of us have been extremely grateful to have so many wonderful opportunities to explore, study, grow, and evolve our own personal yoga practice both as teachers, but more importantly, as students. And throughout this journey, it has become quite apparent to us that every teacher and every class and every moment on the mat can consistently provide new experiences, lessons, and growth. So it was with this deep understanding that we set out to create Boho Beautiful Retreat -¬†immersed in the intention for it to be our humble contribution to anyone's journey whom we might be lucky enough to share it with.¬†

Boho Beautiful Retreat is a yoga journey.

An exploration.

A dedicated & motivated challenge to explore the depths of each of our own physical and mental beings, sewn together by the goal to optimize, expand, and raise the energetic frequency of this life experience.

It is a perfect way to start a new year & a new decade...

title: Yoga For Complete Beginners | Easy Gentle Boho Beautiful Yoga
description:
This yoga for complete beginners class is perfect for anyone that is new to yoga or needing a very gentle and easy yoga class at home. This easy gentle Boho Beautiful yoga class is perfect for beginners to release tension out of the upper body, lower body soreness, or to begin to incorporate gentle movement back into your life.

Throughout this gentle yoga practice for all levels, we will breathe, we will disconnect the mind from the daily mental noise and thought patterns, giving ourselves a moment to be one with ourselves. Whether you are a first-time yoga practitioner, or someone who is looking for a 15 minute easy yoga practice for stress release, this yoga class will give you that opportunity to take all that you need for your needs. 

Being patient and loving will be the key to this yoga practice today. Surrendering and allowing the postures to take you further into this experience of yoga, self-discovery, and inner peace. 
Remember, breathing is a very important factor in any style of yoga. So bring oxygen to your muscles, organs, and mind. Re-energize your nervous system, let go of stress and tension, and become fully present in each moment of each posture as you let go of the past with each exhale you make.

title: BANNED From China?! | Tibet Will Now Always Have Our Heart ‚ù§Ô∏è Boho Diary
description:
BANNED From China?! | Tibet Will Now Always Have Our Heart | Boho Diary

Travelling Tibet was one of those bucket list trips for us. Visiting the Holy City of Lhasa has always been something we were fascinated with. When we finally made it over into Tibet, Lhasa was the first stop and we were forced to recognize that sometimes our expectations are simply a set up to realize that we could have never prepared ourselves for this. The challenges were not only the altitude and the climate but simply being present in an occupied nation and seeing the kindness and hospitality of the Tibetan people even after all the oppression they still suffer through today. This really motivated us to share some light on their story. We had the pleasure of meeting his Holiness the 14th Dalai Lama last year (he was forced to leave Tibet in 1959 and had been living in exile in India ever since) and now returning to his hometown of Lhasa was almost like a completion of our own personal quest to understand a part of this incredible history. 

Although Lhasa didn't live up to our imaginative expectations, once we left and began to travel through the rest of Tibet,  it was like we entered a magical story book. The nature, the animals, the people. Every day it was a new page, a new experience, and a new adventure, thus making Tibet one of the most beautiful places filled with the most magic and energy we've ever experienced. 

#TravelTibet #Lhasa #Tibet

Visit http://www.freetibet.org to learn more about the struggle the Tibetan people are facing today and how you can help.

title: Yin Yoga For Upper Body | Release ALL Your Stress In 20 Minutes
description:
Yin Yoga For Upper Body | Release All Your Stress In 20 Minutes: Boho Beautiful Yoga
This Yin Yoga class for the upper body is going to be fully targeted on releasing tension and stiffness in your neck, shoulders, arms, and upper back. This restorative yoga practice using yin yoga poses to release upper body soreness & stiffness for the physical body, and emotional and mental stress that you may be holding deep within. We will move gently and slowly through each yoga posture and hold selected asanas for two and a half minutes to encourage a really deep myofascial release. 

Remember, breathing is a very important factor in any Yin Yoga class, so throughout this entire practice, make sure you're taking deep breaths in and long, slow exhales out. Bring oxygen to your muscles, organs, and mind. Re-energize your nervous system, let go of stress and tension, and become fully present in each moment of each posture as you let go of the past with each exhale you make. 

Shot in the beautiful nation of Tibet. 
Please check out http://www.freetibet.org

To Get Our Full YIN YOGA Program:
https://shop.bohobeautiful.life/products/complete


What is Yin Yoga?

Yin Yoga is a style of yoga practice that targets the connective tissues, such as the ligaments, bones, and even the joints of the body that normally are not exercised very much in a more active style of asana practice.

Suitable for almost all levels, Yin Yoga is a perfect complement to the dynamic and muscular (yang) styles of yoga that emphasize internal heat, and the lengthening and contracting of our muscles. Yin Yoga generally targets the connective tissues of the hips, pelvis, and lower spine.

Yin Yoga has many amazing benefits but below are some of the key benefits you may begin to feel after a regular yin practice:

-Stillness: calms and balances the mind and body
-Stress and anxiety reduction
-Increased circulation
-Improved flexibility
-Fascial release

Enjoy and let go of all that no longer serves you,

Juliana & Mark

Through gentle movement, this yoga practice for beginners and all levels will focus on increasing flexibility in your hamstrings, stretching different areas of your glute muscles, and opening the hips. The postures will go deep, and we will be stimulating a lot of physical and emotional release of energy of your body, so remember to always be gentle and patient with yourself. Always remember to breathe and stay with your breath. As we go deeper into hip opening yoga asanas, your breath is going to allow you to stay present and release deeper and deeper with time. 

Remember to always listen to your body. If you develop any sharp or shooting pain, take a pause and reset yourself. Never force any postures, but rather simply allow yourself to surrender once you get into a pose. Coming into a meditative state of mind as you hold and let go. 

So get ready to stretch, release, and dive deeper into your hips and hamstrings. 

Namaste xx

Juliana

title: Battling My Addiction | 10 Days In 'Rehab'
description:
There is a time when a habit turns into an addiction, and no matter how big or small, it becomes an issue. Before we can figure out a solution to cure this digital addiction, we must come to the realization that we have a problem. This is not to downplay or minimize other types of what our culture will scream are much more 'serious' physical addictions to the myriad of terrible things that we as human beings find ourselves mixed up with. Those, too, in their own right, need as much attention and loving kindness as possible. But this is to bring to light the idea that first there is a problem, and second, we need to admit it and do something about it sooner rather than later. 

The thing is, we didn't see this coming. And now it has a grip on us so bad - it snuck up like a guerrilla in the night. Its skewed individual's self worth, image, confidence and even will to live. And as a collective, even though it's hard to wrap our heads around the entirety, it's becoming clearer each day that it's affected our democratic process and played a major role in summoning and hypnotizing new violence of all kinds in our streets and in our neighbourhoods. What was once thought to bring us all together and connect us, has severed us from ourselves and each other. It's much more than anyone would have thought when we first picked up our phones, how many years ago now?

Self-awareness is the first step. Monitoring our own behaviour. Recognizing the habits, the triggers, and what the small things are that we can implement into our day to day lives which will help. There are ways to heal, we just need to arrive at the moment in our lives and realize that no one will save us from this social media trap except ourselves. 

BE CONSCIOUS OF YOUR USE
SELF-AWARENESS IS ALWAYS THE FIRST STEP TO CHANGE

Here are a few of our ideas that can help raise more self-awareness as well as give you some space necessary to start recognizing and managing the problem. 

- disconnect your social media for a week and monitor the results
- practice "digital free sundays"
- do not check your phone for as long as possible each morning
- implement a self-imposed phone curfew every night, then shut it off
- do not sleep next to your phone... buy a real alarm clock
- leave it at home when you don't need it
- schedule time to check your phone during the day rather than it scheduling you
- turn OFF notifications
- call people or meet up with them instead of typing
- prioritize nature and leave it behind when you do
- don't charge your phone in the bedroom 
and do your best every time you reach, to be aware of why you are reaching. 

‚ÄòTHE MINUTES‚Äô CALCULATION BREAKDOWN:

Checking social media 6 times a day for ten minutes = 1 hour 
1 hour for 7 days a week = 7 hours per week

1 hour for 30 days a month = 30 hours a month
30 hours a month for a year = 360 hours a year

360 hours divided into 24 hour days = 15 days (when one day = 24 hours)

Note - After all the menial things we as humans have to do in a day (eating, bathing, bathroom, rituals, basic human tasks), we thought calculating a day as a 12 hour day was a fair (and easy) number to work with for the amount of waking hours we have available to chose what we want to spend them on. 

360 hours (on social media a year) divided by 12 hour days 
= 30 days of waking conscious ‚Äôhuman time.' 
AND 30 DAYS EQUALS 1 MONTH!

Therefore, 1 hour a day on social media = 1 month of a calendar year on social media 
(all from checking your social media six times a day for ten minutes each time)

title: When We Stopped Everything To Live With Monks ‚ô• Boho Diary | Kopan Monastery
description:
We found a beautiful way to spend less travelling and acquire more. Not more in experience, but more in depth. Nepal backpack travel offers so many unique ways to experience the incredible culture, mountains, trekking, and the overall Nepalese way of life. So we decided to start our backpacking Asia trip by bringing our lives to a screeching halt and committing 10 days to a Tibetan Buddhist Monastery. Our lives sometimes seem out of control. All about our devices, all about our channel, all about focusing away from ourselves and too much towards things that have unconsciously sucked us in ... so every now and then we have to do something to stop and find the reset button. To breathe and to look inside again, and see what is left to be discovered. And there is always so much. 

So there we were. At Kopan Monastery living, eating, and meditatiting with all the other students, and hundreds of Tibetan monks while taking a Discovering Buddhism Course. What a wild, deep, and meaningful experience. 

At times it was tough... structured religion and dogmatic plausible contradictions. And at other times, it was perspective altering and incredibly valuable to our own spirituality. Just like anything in life, we took what we needed from this wonderful experience of monk life. We discovered the fundamentals of Tibetan Buddhism that placed a lot of life into a beautiful perspective. We cried, we laughed, we were challenged, and we overcame it everything that was brought forward to learn a little bit more of what our Boho Beautiful life is all about.

title: SOCIETY SUCKS SOULS | We Made An Escape Plan & Walked Away üèî Boho Diary Nepal
description:
It's been just over 3 years since we started this channel on a hell bent mission to change our life. We were definitely unhappy and felt the direction of the path that we were headed on wasn't what our souls were asking for. We knew there was more to life than Toronto. More to things than the ego-driven rat race we had found ourselves participating in. So we designed, alchemised, and began our escape. 

This journey has been a roller-coaster of extremes. But so far it has been more fulfilling, exciting, & beautiful a ride than we ever believed we could ask for. 

As we hiked the incredible mountain of Mardi Himal in Nepal, our minds began to go back in time and reflect on this journey that we've set upon. 

Thank you to our friends at Rugged Trails Nepal for the wonderful trip and guidance!
Check Them Out If You Are Looking For A Personalized Hiking Trip in Nepal!!
https://www.ruggedtrailsnepal.com 

May this travel blog/boho diary of our difficult Mardi Himal trek inspire anyone out there who is itching to find a way out of any situation that doesn't fill them up. Our society at times can feel like a cage, imprisoning us in a cycle of debt, bills, mortgage payments, and the constant fear that we don't have enough. Just know there is always a way out, and if there's this burn in your heart and you feel like your soul is being killed by the constant pressures of our western world, then take a moment and realize that anything is possible and that you, too, can figure out a way to pack up and leave. 

We meet people all the time who quit their corporate jobs and move to an island or a smaller town with a slower pace of life. They start a small business, an ice cream shop, they make jewelry and sell it on etsy, they run airbnb's or life coaching online business, etc..etc.

Times are not what they used to be 20 years ago; the boom of the internet has opened the door for so many self made entrepreneurs to be born. So if there's an itch in your heart and a whisper in your soul. Don't drown out the noise, but instead listen closely as it will guide you how to break free and find all that it longs for. 

Love & Light,

Juliana and Mark

title: Terrible Vegans
description:
The Boho Beautiful Vegan Food approach - why we chose this lifestyle, how to travel as a vegan and more questions we get asked when it comes to our food choices.

There's been a lot of drama these days about vegan influencers announcing that they are not vegan anymore, or why they had to alter their vegan/plant-based diets due to their physical and mental issues. We don't want to comment on people's personal choices and controversy but we did want to address a question that many have asked us in the past, such as will we be vegan forever? How do we view the idea of being vegan? Is plant-based eating really good for you? Why are we vegan? How do we survive on a plant-based/vegan diet when travelling the world, especially in third-world countries where vegan options are not easy to find? Well, we finally wanted to address these questions...

title: When Juliana Is Away... | Easy Hair Tutorial For Everyone
description:
My soul is not contained within the limits of my body, my body is contained within the limitlessness of my soul. -Jim Carrey

This idea has been on my mind for a while now. How our appearance, the way we look, the way we dress, the job we hold, all of these and more, create this identity that we tend to become attached to. An attachment that later on begins to bring anxiety and stress into our lives as we begin to witness this body of ours change. And that's the thing, change....the undeniable truth that each and every one of us will encounter. The more we realize that we are not these bodies, that we are not these avatars that we create, but that we are so much greater than our surface. We are energy that was energy before we came into this life and consciousness, and we are the energy that will remain after our eventual end. Once we truly accept that, maybe we can realize that life is just play and that this beautiful existence is simply just one incredible dance and experience in itself.

title: Back Pain & Sciatica Relief ‚ô• Your Daily Yoga Miracle Therapy
description:
New Full Length Fitness Program: https://bohobeautiful.life/transform/

This 30 minute gentle yoga class is designed specifically for anyone suffering from back pain, sciatica pain, or lower body soreness. With a gentle increase of movement, yoga postures, therapeutic strength exercises, we will be gently stimulating the back muscles, stretching the glutes and hamstrings, and giving our body an opportunity to move with care. This yoga class for back pain is also great for anyone suffering from bulging disks or disk herniation.

Its very important that you listen to your body, and if your body responds well to these types of exercises, include them into your life everyday. The glute stretches are great for loosening up the muscles in case your nerve is pinched in that area. The back exercises that include gentle extensions are great for anyone suffering from disk herniation or bulging disks. Try to do these every day to strengthen the muscles around the spine, however avoid rounding out the spine and perhaps even skip the child pose if you do suffer from disk injuries. With daily commitment, with time you will begin to feel an improvement in your back and nerve pain.

During this yoga class for all levels, you will allow your mind and body to connect deeper inward, letting go of any worries or stressful thoughts and truly giving your mind and body the gift of mindful movement, stillness, and healing.  Enjoy and breathe. 

Love & Light...
Juliana & Mark**

title: This Is Territorio De Zaguates  ‚ô• Smooches For 1100 Pooches  (Land Of The Strays)
description:
Please Help The Dogs Of Territorio De Zaguates Survive & Continue... http://www.gofundme.com/bohostrays

Firstly - People are sneaking in at night and poisoning their dogs and your donations will help them secure the grounds to protect themselves. They have already lost so many dogs to this tragedy and are in desperate need to properly secure the premises by adding cameras and movement sensor lamps to the dog living areas and front gates to help protect themselves.

Secondly - Every dollar helps. In North America the average cup of designer coffee costs $5. If each of us sacrifice one coffee each, the difference that could make to the dogs and the sanctuary would be massively HUGE.  

Thirdly - if you are unable to donate at the moment, PLEASE consider sharing this video or fundraiser page on your social media. 

It costs approximately $36 dollars/month to take care of 1 dog - Territorio de Zaguates has 1100 dogs. The math is daunting at best. 

Lya and the dogs always rely on financial assistance and donations for all food, staff, and veterinary expenses, but at the moment, they're also in desperate need of improved infrastructure. Outside of securing the property from trespassers, part of the money from this campaign will go towards:

- The completion of more enclosures and roofing.
- A morgue. :(
- Extensive drainage and runoff modifications.
- To elevate the entire extension of the eating troughs.
- Build a properly equipped "clinic" area where the doctor can operate.
- A specific shed for cleaning materials.
- A specific shed for medicine.
- Tags for all dogs.


YOU CAN ALSO SEND DONATIONS - Dog supplies, toys, tennis balls, blankets, old t-shirts, sheets, crates, vet supplies, anything that might help!

TO SHIP GOODS TO TERRITORIO DE ZAGUATES: 
Please make sure you label all parcels as a GIFT VALUED UNDER $500. Otherwise there will be extra taxes added that the sanctuary is unable to pay to receive your gifts. 

Shipping Label: 
Territorio de Zaguates (Land Of The Strays)
PO Box: 782-1260
Plaza Colonial, Escazu
Costa Rica

So we ask that you open your heart and give whatever you can. 
Even just a few dollars doesn't make a difference to our individual day to day lives but to these dogs and to Lya it means the world. 

Together let's support good people doing good things. 
You and I may not be able to change the entire world but together we can change the entire world of each of these dogs. 

Thank you for standing with us. 

And THANK YOU for considering supporting this campaign. 


Love & Light...
Juliana and Mark

Territorio de Zaguates aka Land Of The Strays is a place like non-other. 378 acres of mountainous fields where 1000's of stray, injured, and abused dogs have come over the last 12 years to learn to be dogs again. All the dogs that have come to this beautiful sanctuary have experienced some kind of human inflicted suffering and abandonment, but here they are given a second chance. With Territorio De Zaguates' numbers now rising to over 1100 free roaming dogs, the costs are rising too and Land Of The Strays needs our help.

title: The Commercialism Plague, We Just Can't  Handle It Anymore ‚ô• Boho Diary | Peru
description:
http://www.bohobeautiful.life

Travelling through the magical cities and villages of Peru's Sacred Valley was incredible. It was such an eye opening experience to be immersed in the Peruvian Inca culture, to meet so many wonderful local people, and to hear their stories of how they truly feel about this commercial boom that has been steadily transforming their world. The exploitation of their sacred plant medicine which is now offered on almost every corner, Starbucks taking out the local coffee shops, McDonalds providing jobs but at the same time destroying other local restaurants, and so many foreign companies creeping their way in to siphon so many dollars away. All of this to serve the massive amount of growing travellers descending upon their sacred spaces.  

So what's the best way to travel in Peru? Or anywhere for that matter? How do you experience the Sacred Valley but at the same time not support the elimination of their culture by the commercialistic ways of the Western world? Should we all just stay at home? Is it better to leave it all be and read about our wonderful world only in Nat Geo? Is there a solution? 

We believe there is. And not just abroad, but in our own communities too. Shop local wherever you go, support community businesses, contribute to the culture that you are surrounding yourself with. Vote with your dollars to keep them in the pockets of those who need it most. And realize that the world has so much to offer with its deep diversity and endless cultural beauty that taking a chance on something new is far more rewarding than the safe familiar road. Its up to all of us. What we value, we can keep alive.

title: AMAZON Rainforest Eco-Bootcamp ‚ô• A Day In The Life
description:
Welcome to the Amazon Rainforest of Peru. Surrounded by amazonian jungle, tucked away on the Amazon River, we filmed this Day In The Life video at the Otorongo Eco-Lodge - whose mission statement is "Promoting the sustainable development of the environment in the Peruvian Amazon since 2016."  Eco-tourism adventure at its finest. 
During this day in our life consisted of amazon jungle rainforest hiking, a fruit tour, swimming in the amazon river next to the pink and grey amazon river dolphins, a night river terror expedition in which we got both stuck and seemingly lost, sunrise amazon bird watching, searchign for tarantulas and poison frogs, and so much more. 

This sustainable eco lodge allowed us not only live in a sustainable and environmentally friendly way but also experience the Amazon in its raw and pure form. We also got to shoot a couple yoga videos too. 

Come along with us and see what a day in the life in the Amazon basin looks like!

title: THIS Juice Cleanse ‚ô• My Story, Weight Loss, & New Me
description:
It‚Äôs very important that throughout our life we always find a way to challenge ourselves. Whether that is our body, our mind or both. Starting a juice cleanse was my first challenge of this year and wow was it an intense journey. It first started as a 3 Day Juice Cleanse and then as day 3 arrived I really felt amazing results, so I kept going and made my 3 day Cleanse to a 7 day Raw Juice Cleanse.


JUICE RECIPES

THE GREEN SUNRISE 
This juice is a great way to start your morning off. It's a heavy vegetable juice with a ton of dense nutrients and a great flavour to help push your body to realize that even with out solid food it can still get all that it needs.

Broccoli- 1/2 a stock of broccoli (stem and all)
Spinach- 1/2 a bunch of spinach
Passion Fruit- Entire fruit (no skin!)
Lemon- 1/2 lemon (rinds and seeds)
Cuccumber- 1/2 to 3/4 cucumber
Add ice to make it come alive. 

THE GREEN BULLET
This juice was awesome. I had it everyday at 11am as a natural sugar life (the pinnacle) and internal reboot (the cayenne). 

Kale - 1/2 a bunch
Ginger- a little chunk
Lemon - 1/2 lemon including seeds and rind
Pineapple - 1/4 to 1/2 a pineapple 
Cucumber- 1/2 to 3/4 of cucumber
Top and stir in 1 table spoon of Cayenne Pepper 
Add ice to really make it refresh.

TUMMERIC FOR DAYS
The main purpose of this juice is the turmeric. Its great for so many reasons (google it!) but I love it for my back as an anti inflammatory. This juice was nice in the afternoon and always seemed to hit the spot. 

Orange- 1 oranges
Lemon- 1/2 lemon
Spinach- 1/4 bunch
Carrot- 2 decent sized carrots
Watermelon- 3 big slices
Turmeric-  As much as I could put in without killing the flavour completely
Fresh Black Pepper- Top the finished juice with a half table spoon of black pepper to supercharge and activate the turmeric. 
Finish with ice cubes to cool it down and make it really enjoyable. 


LIQUID V8 
This was one of the staple dinner juices I worked at getting better and better. The key was experimenting to flavours I would like and trying different combinations of nutrient heavy vegetables. It would usually be the last juice of the day and let my body know once again that it can feel full, nourished, and receive more than it needs in liquid form. 

Tomato- 1 full tomato
Broccoli- 1/2 a stock of broccoli (stock included)
Sweet Pepper- Entire pepper (green, red, or yellow)
Spinach - 1/2 a bunch 
Celery- 2 stalks of celery
Carrot- 2 decent size carrots
Beet- 3/4 beet

title: Pilates Intense Mat Workout ‚ô• Tools For A New You | BELIEF
description:
This class is one of the most effective pilates workout videos we have created for both beginners and advanced. A floor Pilates workout that targets and fine tones different areas of your body which includes your core, obliques, glutes, and hamstrings. Pilates is an incredible way to accomplish real results, weather it's pilates for weight loss, pilates for core strength, or pilates for toning, you can accomplish so much for your body through this circuit of incredibly effective pilates exercises. 

This week the idea we are focussing on in Tools For A New You is ‚Äòbelief‚Äô. What you think about is what you become. Our minds are so powerful, and one of the key ideas that we must always keep within ourselves especially when we embark on any transformational journey is truly believing in ourselves and our strength. In life we will be met with resistance in many shapes and sizes. Weather that is our body‚Äôs limitations, the people around us, or your own ego telling you that achieving your goal is not possible for someone like ‚Äúyou‚Äù. Take a deep breath, and allow those thoughts or people around you to fade away as background noise. Find the strength within yourself and believe that no matter how hard it gets, you are strong enough and capable of achieving anything you put your mind into. Always reminding yourself that as long as you believe in it, as long as you are putting all the hard work and energy into your goals and dreams nothing can stop you from achieving that which you deserve, not even your mind. So brush off the negative self talk, pick yourself up if you fall down, and never stop believing in the idea that you deserve to live a happy, healthy, and prosperous existence.

description:

Focusing on fusing Vinyasa based flow (Yang) with slow and tension releasing postures (Yin), this class is great to do in morning as well as anytime during the day as we focus on first warming up the body with a flow, and then taking it into a deep release of the glutes and hamstrings.

title: Van Life & The Lessons Of The Road ‚ô• Boho Diary | USA
description:
After converting our van into a tiny home, we embarked on a new adventure: the Boho Beautiful Positive Movement Tour. 3 months of travelling across the USA took us to 40 different cities, and with our coordinators and all the people who came out we were all able to raise over $20,000 for local non-profit animal welfare organizations through the charity yoga classes, and conquered over 10,000 miles in our newly converted camper van (talk about tiny van life living).  

Through this digital nomadic lifestyle we finally got to experience what "vanlife" was truly about. The ups and downs of tiny living, to exhausting drives, to uplifting human connections... all of this was something we will forever remember. 

Thank you and stay tuned for more from our wild nomadic travel adventures! XO

Juliana and Mark

title: Our Incredible Van Conversion & Tiny Living Tour ‚ô• 12 Passenger To A Solar Camper
description:
A Boho Beautiful Travel diary about the Positive Movement Tour and the van we lived in during our time on the road. It has been a dream of ours and thanks to our friends Kyle & Sarah it turned into reality- we are ready to tour the states!              
 
Our store: https://bohobeautiful.life/our-store/

We have embarked on a new journey- camper van life. As we prepared to travel through North America in our van for our Positive Movement Tour, we had some help from our friend Kyle and his wonderful wife Sarah to convert it into an incredible tiny home on wheels. 9000 miles in our stealth camper converted van, we are truly experiencing a new nomadic lifestyle. Oh... and this tiny home has solar power!

How to handle the nomadic van lifestyle is a new territory we are exploring, which includes embracing minimalism, tiny living, and stealth camping wherever we can. But so far it has been nothing but incredible memories and adventures since we sold everything we owned and drove off into the unknown.  in full. Here's to new sunsets and sunrises. And we hope you enjoy our Incredible van conversion & tiny living tour XO

If you are interested in getting your van/bus converted feel free to reach out to Kyle & Sarah: KyleNight@hotmail.com

Good friend's rad soccer company- www.LifeIsAKick.com

title: This Is The End For A While ‚ô• Boho Diaries | Ep.14 Planet Earth
description:
It's a special opportunity to be able to control how something you care deeply about will end. It wasn't easy but we have decided that we would rather tie it up properly than let the Boho Diary Series go on for too long.  That is not to say we might not start a second series down the line just like it, and we are definitely NOT stopping making youtube content for you all, but we are peacefully putting the final chapter of this series out into the universe. 

Thank you so much to every single one of you who connected, enjoyed, and allowed our journey in South East Asia to affect you in any way at all. We will continue bringing you all more yoga, fitness, food, life, and meditation videos however, as far as Boho Diaries go, this is it for a while. 

Having to returned to North America we are now about to embark on a new adventure, The Boho Beautiful Positive Movement Tour 2017! 40 stops across USA, 3 months on the road in our van with our dog. A new van life ahead of us with triumphs, struggles, new connections, and memorable experiences. 

 Here‚Äôs to new adventures and never forgetting the past adventures that got us here. XO

With love,

Juliana & Mark


Shot: 
in Siem Reap Cambodia and on route back to Canada.

title: Our Morning Routine ‚ô• Boho Diaries | Ep.12 Thailand
description:
The simplicity of life is something we're always trying to grasp. Living on an island where dogs rule the beaches and motor bikes are your only way of transportation has taught us a lot. There's something really special in finding a routine that fuels your mind, body, and soul. Once you find that, never let it go. Let it help you grow in ways that allows you to find more meaning and purpose in every breath you take. And when you falter from it, as we always will, accept the step back and take two more forward as you should- remembering how you found it or maybe even how it found you. 

Love. Light. & Happiness To All! XO

Juliana and Mark

Shot on the islands of Koh Mak, Koh Kood, & Koh Kham in Thailand.

title: For The Love Of Elephants, Please! ‚ô• Boho Diaries | Ep.11 Elephant Haven Thailand
description:
Thank you from the bottom of our hearts to all the incredible donors, people that shared our video, and simply spread the word about the current elephant crisis going on in this world. The money we raised together with you guys may not change the world, but it will change these elephants world. SO again thank you for opening your hearts and wallets. This is just the beginning....until every chain is broken. 

Elephant Haven Thailand (Kanchanaburi) is part of the Elephant Nature Park organization based in Chang Mai, and although Elephant Haven was once a trekking camp providing tourists with elephant riding and entertainment, it has since been converted into a place where elephants can recover in peace and be elephants again. 

The business of people using Elephants to acquire easy tourist dollars is ugly, abusive, shameful, and unfortunately quite profitable‚Ä¶ but places like Elephant Haven & Elephant Nature park serve both as sanctuaries for these animals and as necessary experiential education for tourists and animal lovers alike. They help shine a light on the need for us to reevaluate our relationships to this planet‚Äôs most wonderful creatures. 


For More Information on the crisis and how you can help or get involved please visit:

https://www.elephantnaturepark.org

http://www.saveelephant.org

http://www.elephanthaventhailand.org

title: Ultimate Butt Challenge ‚ô• Glutes, Hamstrings & Quads | Koh Kut
description:
Challenge Description Below!!

Back by popular demand this is your ultimate "butt lift, glute building, leg toning - whatever you prefer to call it" challenge! If you stick to this challenge you will begin to see incredible definition and toning in that area of your body. This workout is not going to be easy so please be patient with yourself. As the muscles get stronger, the exercises will get easier and the results will begin to show.

 Don't worry if you have to take breaks or even stop during the exercises for the first week or so. Its completely normal to feel your muscles become fatigued, therefore adding some of the recommended yoga classes along with the challenge is highly recommended to avoid muscle soreness. 

Be strong, be patient, work hard, and have fun! 


---THE 2 WEEK CHALLENGE---


‚ô• WEEK 1 ‚ô• 
One Set = One time through the video: 20 min total glute workout*

Day 1: One Set + followed by the yoga video below:

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6F0l9lVnKdQ

Day 6 : Day Off- Complete 1 Yoga Class from the list below*

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xcMOYrdHrkE

Week 1 Yoga Class Suggestions:

Relaxing Yoga For Peace:

Perfect Yoga For Everyone:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BeG_UU-Bf5k

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=koUi-AgsowQ


‚ô• WEEK 2 ‚ô• 
Adding some more body toning to continue to challenge the body*

Day 8: One Set + Arm Toning Video:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=W2Mq_c-dgVY

Day 9: Day Off- Complete 1 Yoga Class from the list below*

‚ô• DAY OFFS ‚ô• 
This is your time to let the muscles rest. However, including a yoga class will make sure the muscles get time to recover and release any built up lactic acid through deep yoga stretches. So pick one class from the suggested video list below each week to choose a yoga video thats right for you. 

‚ô• CHALLENGE GUIDELINES ‚ô•
  
‚ô• Drink at least 2 L of water per day through the challenge.

‚ô• Get at least 8 hours of sleep per night so your muscles have time to recover and rest. 

‚ô• And always remember one last thing, if you want the best results you have to apply 2 rules and stick to them: You have to work hard AND eat clean.  I eat a plant based diet which helps a lot and I highly recommend it. But the working hard piece comes from within each of us... you have to commit yourself everyday to the idea of achieving whatever healthy look you desire.

title: Yin Yoga Class ‚ô• Release Stress & Feel Amazing in 30 Minutes | Borneo
description:
This Yin Yoga class is one of the best ways to not only increase flexibility in your legs and hips but it will also help you release any stored up negative energy in your body. Emotional energy, (if not dealt with or released) overtime will manifest as physical illness in your body. Whether that is as sickness, or simple muscles aches and tension. 
By holding each posture in this yin yoga class bring your awareness to anything that you believe no longer serves you. As you exhale, visualize this negative energy leaving your body and breath in positive and peaceful energy. Releasing any stress or worry and filling your mind and body with positive high frequency vibrations. 

What is Yin Yoga?

Yin Yoga is a style of yoga practice that targets the connective tissues, such as the ligaments, bones, and even the joints of the body that normally are not exercised very much in a more active style of asana practice.

Suitable for almost all levels, Yin Yoga is a perfect complement to the dynamic and muscular (yang) styles of yoga that emphasize internal heat, and the lengthening and contracting of our muscles. Yin Yoga generally targets the connective tissues of the hips, pelvis, and lower spine.

Each posture in Yin Yoga is usually held up to 5 min or so. However, if you're very new to this I recommend you start with the 1-2 min holds until you feel more confident in your posture. If you're more of an advanced yogi then feel free to pause the video and hold each pose longer. 

Yin Yoga has many amazing benefits but below are some of the key benefits you may begin to feel after a regular yin practice:

-Stillness: calms and balances the mind and body
-Stress and anxiety reduction
-Increased circulation
-Improved flexibility
-Fascial release

Enjoy and let go of all that no longer serves you,

Juliana & Mark

title: Yoga For Splits ‚ô• Release Tight Hips & Increase Leg Flexibility
description:
This yoga flow is perfect for those of you that have always wanted to achieve the splits or if you‚Äôre simply looking to gain more flexibility in your legs and open up the hips. The different postures that will be included in this particular flow will help you loosen the hamstrings, loosen tight hips, and let go of any tension within your lower body. If you are looking to attain fast results in your leg flexibility, we highly recommend doing this video at least 4-5 times per week so you can really start to train and loosen the lower body. A great time to do this flow would be after a tough workout or in the morning when you want to get the juices flowing and the body fully awake to start the day. 

Make sure you take your time with the stretches. Don‚Äôt push too much, too fast. Try to attain a position where you are able to hold the posture without too much pain. Speaking of pain, never push through any sharp, electric, or shooting pain. That is what we call the ‚Äúbad pain‚Äù as it is usually your body letting you know that you are going too far for what it can handle and this can potentially cause injury. Listen to your body, breathe, and take your time. Be patient, stay dedicated to daily practice and you will get the results you are looking for. 

Namaste XO

Juliana

title: Yoga For Mindfulness ‚ô•  Silence Your Chattering Thoughts & Anxiety | Gili Asahan
description:
This yoga class is all about allowing yourself to immerse in the present moment. Being mindful of your breath as you move and hold each posture. With each exhale letting go of any negative stressful energy and with each inhale bringing in positive, peaceful, and warm energy. 

It's important for each of us to take a moment for ourselves each day. Whether it be in the morning, afternoon or evening. A simple 15-20 minute self time out will help you rebalance your mind, body, and spirit. 

So find a quiet space, turn off your phone, and join me on this beautiful deserted island in be Gili Islands of Indonesia.

Instructor: Juliana Spicoluk

title: Hospitalized in Lombok ‚ô• Boho Diaries | Ep.6 Mataram
description:
It's crazy how getting really sick can help you really appreciate something we tend to forget about while we're concerned with much of our daily life and trivial challenges or successes...our health. This was a true test of Indonesia, sending both of us off the boat and into the emergency hospital... life is a magical adventure in every way thats for sure. And even in it's worst we must find the lessons it brings forward. 

We're happy, healthy, and much better now! The Lombok medical services were first class. :D

title: People Leaving Our Channel?! It's Worth It ‚ô• Boho Diaries | Ep.5 Gili Air
description:
We've finally made it out of the busy streets of Ubud and found our temporary little home on a beautiful island called Gili Air. This place is magical, the people are all wonderful, we never want to leave. 

We have saved/sponsored a dying kitten, soaked in salty ocean water, made beautiful connections with people, taught beach yoga classes to new friends, and felt like we were part of a new family for a week. 

Life is a beautiful adventure. 

If you're interested in joining the Gili Shark Conservation Team check out their website:
 
http://gilisharkconservation.com

If you're ever in Gili Air make sure you stay at Villa Nangka: 
http://villanangkagiliair.com

If you like to try sub winging like Mark is doing in the beginning of the video check out this link below:

http://www.subwinggiliislands.com

PUDJA!  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pm_tGUNpQoQ 

Love and Light,

Juliana and Mark

title: Depression, Back Injury, & Healing From Within ‚ô• Boho Diaries | Ep.3 Bali Confessions
description:
We have been yearning for an escape from the concrete jungle, the commercialism, the seemingly backwards society that we often felt like we were trapped in. Moving to the Rocky Mountains was wonderful and it gave us a moment to stop and take a breath, but now we're in need of more then just a breath of fresh air, we're in need of learning how to breathe again. 

We have finally arrived in Bali. Reflecting on the years and the last few months that brought us here has begun to make it quite apparent that we have our work set out for us. And not work such as our business and brand, but self work. Self work through self care will truly be the theme of the next few months. 

May we look back at this period of our life one day and continue to smile. ‚ô•

Thank you for being here with us... 

Love,
Juliana and Mark

title: Three Hot Springs In One Day ‚ô• Radium Hot Springs, Fairmont, & Lucier River
description:
All within close to an hour of each other, Radium Hot Springs, Lucier River & Hot Springs, & Fairmont Hot Springs sit in the Kootenay Valley in south eastern British Columbia.  While staying in Invermere we figured, why not try to go to all three in one day. And so it went... 

Lucia Hot Springs is a natural hot spring which comes out of a rock bed and flows into the river. Fairmont is owned privately. And Radium is part of Kootenay national park.

In the end our bodies felt like tapioca pudding but it was definitely a day well spent. We slept incredibly well that night. :) 

love and light,
... Juliana & Mark*

title: What I Eat In A Day ‚ô• Healthy Vegan Comfort Food | Rocky Mountains
description:
A Boho Beautiful Vegan Food diary. 
What we eat in a day in the Rocky Mountains. All recipes are easy, healthy & vegan.

Our store: www.bohobeautiful.life

Living in the mountains is forcing us to find everything we can to keep us warm and of course that includes the food we eat. 

This video was sponsored by Thrive Market to show you what we cook and eat on a regular day in the mountains. Thrive Market is a great new online store that sells the top organic and healthy products at wholesale prices shipped straight to your door!

The detailed ingredient list and measurements to the meals we made in this video are below.

 Enjoy!! 

‚ô• Blueberry Chia Pancakes ‚ô•

Ingredients: 

Dry:

1 cup         Spelt Flour
2 tbsp        Chia Seeds
2 tbsp        Hemp Seeds
1/2 tbsp    Baking Powder
1 tsp          Salt
1 cup         Blueberries (fresh or frozen)

Liquid:
1 cup   Almond Milk 
1 tsp    Apple Cidere Vinegar
1 tsp    Vanilla Extract
2 tbsp  Maple Syrup

‚ô• Spinach Avocado Smoothie ‚ô•

Garnish with: Cacao Nibs, Hemp Seeds, or Blackberries

title: Giving Up Everything To Wanderlust ‚ô• Boho Diaries | Ep 2. Invermere BC
description:
Our first days of being free. Living in an off the grid cabin in the mountains. :)

Well, we've made it to our first temporary home, an off the grid cabin in the Rocky Mountains. We have finally finished the long two week drive through snowy Canada and are excited to settled for a short time before we take off again. 

Living off the grid is a new experience for us that's for sure, however, we are starting to really love it here. 

A simpler way of life. Starting to remember what's it's like to listen to real silence again, look at a sky covered with sparkling stars, experiencing the deep freeze of the mountains, and allowing that feeling that we're not coming back truly set in. 

Hope you enjoy Part 2 of the Boho Diaries. We made it to our first stop, where to next...?

Love,

Mark and Juliana

title: Challenge Your Waistline ‚ô• Abs & Core Workout Plan
description:
This 21 day Ab Challenge is a little different then some of the other challenges that we've done before. So read the description carefully, and get ready to sweat!


The Rules:
The only rule to this challenge is that everyday you're going to push yourself a little further then the day before. So grab a pen and paper so at the end of each day you can keep track of where you stopped to reference when you start the next day. 


The Schedule: 
The schedule for this challenge will be 2 days of core work and 1 day of yoga for 3 weeks. which will mean your core is becoming stronger and stronger with each day! 


The Goal:
The goal here is to build the strength in your core, to trim the waistline, and to help you get that ab definition a lot of us strive to achieve. 


DAY ITINERARY:

Day 1: 
Do this workout as far as your feel the strength of your body can take you, and then stop. If you stop three minutes in, thats completely ok. If you finish the entire class once through completely, start it up a second time and continue till you have to stop. Listen to your body, and make sure to stop when it tells you. 

Day 2: 
Do it again, but use the day before as a marker point and make sure you make it to at least to the same spot if not further. 

Day 3: 
Take a break and replace this workout with any of the following yoga classes below...

Relaxing Yoga For Peace ‚ô• 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IYiV4ztPVu0

Stress Relief Yoga ‚ô• 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SHdwAsUtRBg

Yin Yoga Class ‚ô• 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BsKUBO_TPRk

Perfect Yoga For Everyone ‚ô• 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oA6vjBPlmCE

Best Yoga For The Heart ‚ô• 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2b794DpXLJw

Yoga For Sleep ‚ô• 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=txasA5fOtGI

Easy Yoga For Beginners ‚ô• 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6F0l9lVnKdQ


Day 4: 
Come back to this class and make sure you go even further than the last time you did it (Day 2). 

Day 5 & Onward:
Continue to cycle two days of this video and one day of yoga for 21 days. Always mark down where you made it to. And always make sure to match that spot or go further the next day when you come back to this class. 

REMEMBER- 
If you make it to the end of the class, you are not done yet! You have to start the class up again and go until you have to stop. That's the name of the game. 

Good luck with the challenge! Let us know how it goes for you... let's get those abs nice and strong!! 

- Juliana and Mark

title: We Sold Everything & Left ‚ô• Boho Diaries |  Ep 1. Goodbye Toronto
description:
Yes, it is true. We have sold all of our belongings, quit our jobs in Toronto, bought a used van, got our dog, a suitcase each, some filming gear and off we go.

Life has blessed us with opportunities so that we can make a step forward in exploring this beautiful unpredictable adventure called life. And our hearts are filled with pure gratitude for how this amazing adventure has opened up for us.

Is it scary to leave like that? I can‚Äôt say it‚Äôs not. Its scary changing your life. Stepping forward into the complete unknown, without a plan, a security line, or a plan B ready to be played. But at the same time I‚Äôve never felt so liberated in my life. And every time someone asks so where will you go next, it‚Äôs thrilling to hear ourselves stutter on the words, ‚Äúwe don‚Äôt know.‚Äù

No more attachments, just our love, our dog, and this beautiful experience of existence. We‚Äôre about to drive upon an empty road that will lead us to beautiful, adventurous, frighting, and awakening experiences.

Follow our diaries...

Love,

Mark and Juliana

title: What I Eat In A Day ‚ô• Easy Healthy Vegan Meals | Canada
description:
https://www.bohobeautiful.life

Since spending our summer in our home country, Canada, we decided it was time to share another video on the food we love to eat and cook. We hope this video gives you a little insight into our vegan lifestyle and how easy it to create delicious and nutritious meals. 

Enjoy the recipes and we highly recommend you try them out at home as well. Below are the recipes to the meals made in this video. Enjoy!!

Chia Pudding ‚ô• 

Ingredients:

2 cups coconut milk
1/2 cup Chia Seeds
1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract
1/2 cup fresh/frozen Strawberries
1 Tbsp Cacao Nibs 

Directions:

1. Blend all ingredients together except the chia seeds. 
2. Mix chia seeds into the blended mixture .
3. Place the entire mixture into a glass container in a fridge overnight 
    or at least 4 hours. 
4. When ready to enjoy, garnish with some fresh fruit and cacao nibs. 

Smoothie Bowl ‚ô• 

Ingredients:

1.5 cup Frozen Strawberries 
2 Bananas
1/2 cup Hemp Seeds
1 tsp Spirulina 
1 cup Unsweetened Almond Milk 
1 tbsp Raw Almond Butter 
1 cup  Ice 

Garnish:

1/2 cup Granola Mix
1/2 cup Raisin Nut Mix (cashews/almonds/seeds)
1 tbsp Raw cocoa nibs
1 tbsp  Hemp Seeds 

Note: Mix it up with adding fruit if you crave 
something more sweet. 

Directions:

1. Blend all ingredients together except garnish. 
2. Place Garnish on top. 

Spinach & Arugula Roasted Almond Salad ‚ô•

 Ingredients:

2 cup Fresh Spinach
1 cup Arugula
1/2 cup Sliced Cucumber 
1/4 cup Roasted Almonds/Pecans
1/2 Apple (sliced)
1 tbsp  Hemp Hearts

Dressing:

2 tbsp  Olive Oil
1/2tsp  Apple Cider Vinegar 
1tsp  Agave Syrup
1/4  Lemon  Juice(squeezed)
1/2 tsp  Dried Basil 

Directions:

1. Slice apple and cucumbers
2. Mix all the ingredients together. 
3. Cover with dressing.
4. Sprinkle hemp seeds on top

Roasted Almonds ‚ô• 

Ingredients:

2 cups Almonds
3 tbsp Agave Syrup/Honey=
dash Cayenne Pepper

Directions:

Liquid Mixture:
1. Mix ingredients 
2. Microwave for 30 seconds. 
3. Pre-head oven to 400 F.
4. Place almonds on parchment paper and cover with mixture.
5. Bake 12-15 min. Checking in from time to time. 

Roasted Quinoa Stuffed Peppers ‚ô• 

Ingredients:

4 Bell Peppers (any colour)
1 1/2 cups Quinoa 
1 cup  Tomato Sauce 
1/2 cup White Cap Mushrooms (chopped)
1 Onion (chopped)
1 Large Carrot (finely chopped)
1/2 tsp Garlic Powder
1 tsp  Basil
1/2 tsp Ground Cumin
1/2 tsp Cayenne Pepper
1/4 tsp Ground Black Pepper

Directions:

1. Cut the tops of the peppers, leaving the caps aside. 
2. Scoop the seeds out of the peppers, leaving them hollow. 
3. Simmer quinoa on medium-low heat until cooked. 
4. Stir-fry the vegetables adding the tomato sauce and at the end the quinoa. Mix all ingredients together. 
5. Fill the empty peppers with the mixture, placing the pepper caps on top. 
6. Pre-heat oven to 350F. Placing the peppers into a casserole dish,cover with a lid. 
7. Bake for 50min - 55 min. 
8. Remove the lid and broil with pepper cap on for 5 min before removing the peppers. 

Thanks so much for watching and we hope you enjoy trying out these recipes at home!
